ion of antidepressants, Ecks theorizes value as a process of biocommensuration. Biocommensurations—transactions that aim or claim to make life better—are those forms of social, medical, and corporate actions that allow value to be measured, exchanged, substituted, and redistributed. Ecks’s theory expands value beyond both a Marxist labor theory of value and a free market subjective theory, thereby offering new insights into how the value of lives and things become entangled under neoliberal capitalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAntidepressantsxEconomic aspectszIndia. 0aAntidepressantszIndia. 0aDepressed personszIndia. 0aDepression, MentalxTreatmentzIndia. 0aMental healthxEconomic aspectszIndia. 0aPharmaceutical industryxEconomic aspectszIndia. 0aPharmaceutical industryxMoral and ethical aspectszIndia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022282?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022282423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022282/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  a